		<id>http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=169224#p169224</id>
		<link href="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=169224#p169224"/>
		<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Pure Lua port of the sfxr sound generator]]></title>

		
		<content type="html" xml:base="http://love2d.org/forums/viewtopic.php?p=169224#p169224"><![CDATA[
Bumping a bit, also I added functions for generating a simple Lua file from the sound parameters and for loading it. You can use it like this if you want to work with the Löve file API instead of the basic Lua one:<br><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>local sound = sfxr.newSound()sound:randomize()local f = love.filesystem.newFile("sound.lua")f:open("w")sound:save(f)f:flush()f:close()</code></pre></div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>local sound = sfxr.newSound()local f = love.filesystem.newFile("sound.lua")f:open("r")sound:load(f)f:close()sound:play()</code></pre></div>If you pass a second argument to sound:save(), it will generate a somewhat smaller file because no indention and linebreaks are added.<br>Here are the results of these examples, compressed and uncompressed:<div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>local s={ change={  amount=0.39114666484126;  speed=0.53098955685005; }; vibrato={  delay=-0.94992868273876;  depth=-0.024465061542777;  speed=0.84200208799958; }; frequency={  slide=-0.027968131846831;  limit=0;  start=0.23970054770736;  dslide=0.59757475861064; }; phaser={  sweep=0.4304590939705;  offset=-0.070899490398386; }; duty={  ratio=-0.3660692363753;  sweep=-0.5988394794907; }; repeatspeed=0.62650828993079; highpass={  sweep=-0.19473133535069;  cutoff=0.6262447349085; }; envelope={  attack=0.044302194827103;  punch=0.011362092672399;  decay=-0.55449086076159;  sustain=0.47922909089777; }; volume={ }; lowpass={  resonance=-0.0013938250035848;  sweep=2.243246748532e-006;  cutoff=0.67252042718807; };};return s, "0.0"</code></pre></div><div class="codebox"><p>Code: </p><pre><code>local s={change={amount=0.39114666484126;speed=0.53098955685005;};vibrato={delay=-0.94992868273876;depth=-0.024465061542777;speed=0.84200208799958;};frequency={slide=-0.027968131846831;limit=0;start=0.23970054770736;dslide=0.59757475861064;};phaser={sweep=0.4304590939705;offset=-0.070899490398386;};duty={ratio=-0.3660692363753;sweep=-0.5988394794907;};repeatspeed=0.62650828993079;highpass={sweep=-0.19473133535069;cutoff=0.6262447349085;};envelope={attack=0.044302194827103;punch=0.011362092672399;decay=-0.55449086076159;sustain=0.47922909089777;};volume={};lowpass={resonance=-0.0013938250035848;sweep=2.243246748532e-006;cutoff=0.67252042718807;};};return s, "0.0"</code></pre></div><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://love2d.org/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=134808">nucular</a> — Thu Jun 05, 2014 8:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
